data.title: 准备以至少30秒的时间回答以下问题
data.answer: We can see a graffito on the wall. The main character is a monster who has an elephant's face and octopus's feet. This picture is very creative yet scary. If such animals exist, they must be very dangerous for humans. But I don't feel that graffiti should be considered a form of vandalism, but as a type of street art that others can appreciate, even if it's illegal. Graffito provides a way for people to express themselves openly. It helps people make a statement about what they believe in. This is one of the primary purposes of art. (98 words)
